dxf2svg.util.wiretrace
Class WireLabelLocation

java.lang.Object
  dxf2svg.util.wiretrace.WireLabelLocation
public class WireLabelLocation
extends java.lang.Object

This class encapsulates an SvgObject which should be a wire (or gang) and stores it and the integer value or either START_POINT or END_POINT of where the label can be found. These values refer to the logical start and end points of the wire. The START_POINT is defined as the end opposite of the 'SHEET [n]' label. The END_POINT is defined as the end of the wire beside the 'SHEET [n]' label. This object contains the wire, the label location and any wire ID number as an SvgText element.

Version:
0.04 - September 6, 2005
Author:
Andrew Nisbet
See Also:

Constructor Detail

WireLabelLocation

public WireLabelLocation(SvgDoubleEndedGraphicElement element,
                         int whichEnd)
Takes a wire from and stores it and the location of the wire label either the start or end of the wire; the wire's ID will be at the other end.

Parameters:
element - The wire being stored probably a polyline, but could be any SvgDoubleEndedGraphicElement.
whichEnd - START_POINT is the label was found at the start of the wire and END_POINT if the label (SHEET 2) was found at the end of the wire.
Method Detail

setId

public void setId(SvgText id,
                  boolean isDebugMode)
Allows the wire to take a wire id number as a String and applies it as an ID attribute to the element. Note: if a new ID object is passed but is null the the value is ignored.

Parameters:
id - id of the wire
isDebugMode - If true the id is set via SvgElement.setObjID(java.lang.String) method and if false a new Attribute is added. This is done so we don't get duplicate ID tags if the DEBUG switch is set.

isIdFlagSet

public boolean isIdFlagSet()
Returns true if the ID for this object has been set and false otherwise.

getWireLabelLocation

public int getWireLabelLocation()
Returns the end of the wire where the wire id number is expected to be found. If the label was found at the end of the wire, then the wire ID number will be found at the start point.

Returns:
Location of the 'SHEET [n]' label. Either the wires START_POINT or END_POINT

getWireIntersection

public Point getWireIntersection(int which)
Returns any intersection point of this objects wire. If the requested intersection is out of range null will be returned.

Parameters:
which - the Point you require. If you require the logical start point (defined as the end opposite of the 'SHEET [n]' label then use START_POINT. If you require the logical end Point, use END_POINT. Any other integer will return the requested point from the wire or null if the requested number is out of range of the number of intersections. NOTE: intersection points are numbered from 0 to n-1.
Returns:
point The requested intersection Point of the wire or null if out of range.
